A) Redis + Docker + Spring Cache (team guide)
1) Start Redis (Docker)
Open terminal:

docker run -d --name redis-cache -p 6379:6379 redis:latest

Next time onwards:
docker start redis-cache

Check running:
docker ps

Test Redis:docker exec -it redis-cache redis-cli
Expected: PONG

Output must be:
PONG

Exit:
exit

âœ… Redis is now running on localhost:6379.

2) Spring setup (very short)

Add Redis + Cache dependency (2 lines in pom).
In application.properties put redis host/port + ttl (10m).
Add @EnableCaching in main app OR config class.